<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-347-528  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 347 528.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 9 1990 n362 p113(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Video-imaging system from ATandamp;T VAR aids police. (ATandamp;T Corp.andO;Authorized System Marketer Information Retrieval Imaging Systems'Vision criminal identification software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doyle, T.C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ATandamp;T's Authorized System Marketer Information Retrieval ImagingSystems (IRIS) has developed the Vision MSDOS-based softwarepackage that is being used by criminal investigators to identifynarcotics traffickers.andP;  Vision has been used by the San FranciscoPolice Department since 1989 and is credited with identifyingseveral criminals who may otherwise have escaped detection.andP;  IRISwas founded by 21-year-old Chuck Davis, who says the system wascreated initially to help find missing children, but San FranciscoPolice Lieutenant James Molinari saw the system and knew it hadpotential for tracking criminals.andP;  Vision captures digital imagesand stores them for later display; on-screen photo lineups can becreated for identifying criminals.andP;  The system is also used tostore videos taken by drug traffickers of their activities.andO;Interest in the system has grown throughout the Bay Area and topolice departments throughout the US.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Information Retrieval Imaging Systems (products).andO;Product:   Vision (Computer program) (usage).andO;Topic:     Law EnforcementDrug AbuseSoftware PackagesImaging TechnologyVideo RecordingsData BasesMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>